==English==
===Etymology===
{{L.}} ''[[com-]]'', with + ''[[panis]]'', bread
===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-companion.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

#a [[friend]], [[acquaintance]], or [[partner]]; someone with whom one spends [[time]] or keeps [[company]]
#:''His dog has been his trusted '''companion''' for the last five years.''
#(''dated'') a person [[employ]]ed to [[accompany]] or [[travel]] with another
#{{nautical}} The [[framework]] on the [[quarterdeck]] of a [[sailing ship]] through which [[daylight]] entered the [[cabin]]s below
#{{nautical}} The [[covering]] of a [[hatchway]] on an upper deck which leads to the [[companionway]]; the [[stairs]] themselves

